那时候我很需要钱

10
00:03:18,294 --> 00:03:22,207
After going door-to-door all day, I was back again at Joppy's bar...
在摈家摈户地技工作后我又回到了佐皮的小酒馆里

11
00:03:22,414 --> 00:03:25,724
... trying to figure out where to look for work the next day.
好好的想想我第二天该去哪里技工作

12
00:03:26,214 --> 00:03:29,445
The newspapers was going on and on about the city elections...
每一份报纸上都是关于市长选举的事．．

13
00:03:29,654 --> 00:03:32,293
... like they was really gonna change somebody's life.
好像他们真的能够改变某人的一生似的．

14
00:03:32,494 --> 00:03:36,692
My life had already changed when I lost my job 3 weeks before.
自从3个星期以前我丢了工作以后我的生活倒是真的改变了

15
00:03:36,894 --> 00:03:41,410
For example, one of the white guys pulls a double shift.
假如是一个白人家伙一天轮两次班

16
00:03:41,694 --> 00:03:45,289
lf he says he's too tired to work overtime, you don't fire them.
如果他说他已经厌倦了加班你们应该不会解雇他吧

17
00:03:45,654 --> 00:03:47,406
That's all you have to say?
你要说的就只有这些?

18
00:03:56,574 --> 00:03:58,769
No, that's not all. l need....
不，还有．我得

19
00:04:01,494 --> 00:04:04,611
l need to pay my mortgage and eat.
我还要还贷款，吃饭

20
00:04:05,574 --> 00:04:09,567
l need a house to live in and clothes on my back. l need the job.
我要住，要穿．我需要钱

21
00:04:10,294 --> 00:04:12,854
l'm sorry, fella, l gotta get back to work.
我很抱歉，伙计我要回去工作了

22
00:04:16,614 --> 00:04:18,252
My name's not ''fella.''
我的名字不叫”伙计

23
00:04:20,294 --> 00:04:24,253
My name's not ''fella.'' My name is Ezekiel Rawlins.
我的名字不叫”伙计我叫做伊泽科尔．g林斯

24
00:04:25,094 --> 00:04:26,812
Catch you later, Joppy.
佐皮，我迟点再付你钱

25
00:04:27,054 --> 00:04:30,012
Watch the marble, damn it! What'd l tell you?
小心我的大理石桌面该死的 你有什么看法

26
00:04:35,374 --> 00:04:38,252
How much you think they're paying at Douglas Aircraft?
你觉得道格拉斯飞机公司的薪水应该是多少

27
00:04:38,494 --> 00:04:39,722
l don't know.
我不知道

28
00:05:07,014 --> 00:05:08,163
Come on over here.
过来

29
00:05:08,654 --> 00:05:10,610
There's somebody l want you to meet.
我介绍一个人给你认识

30
00:05:14,894 --> 00:05:16,805
Come on, this is a friend of mine.
过来，这是我的朋友

31
00:05:18,574 --> 00:05:20,644
Easy, this is Mr. Albright.
伊斯，这是奥尔布莱特先生

32
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:23,243
-Call me DeWitt, Easy. -How you doing?
叫我戴维新伊斯你好

33
00:05:23,454 --> 00:05:24,523
Take a seat.
坐

34
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:30,246
Mr. Albright and me...
奥尔布莱特先生和我

35
00:05:30,494 --> 00:05:32,883
...go way back to before the war.
还没有上战场就回来了

36
00:05:33,294 --> 00:05:35,808
Back when l was still in the fight game.
应该是我还在战场上的时候你就回来了

37
00:05:36,094 --> 00:05:38,005
Ever seen this guy fight?
你看过这个家伙打仗的样子吗?

38
00:05:40,734 --> 00:05:44,090
Every time Joppy stepped in the ring, you knew you would see...
每一次佐皮踏进包围圈的时候你应该也能猜到会发生什么事

39
00:05:44,294 --> 00:05:46,854
...some knockdown-dragout fisticuffs.
锐不可当D拼命的挥动着他的拳

40
00:05:47,494 --> 00:05:49,724
-Where you from? -Houston.
D你的老家在哪?D休斯顿

41
00:05:51,654 --> 00:05:53,292
Joppy's hometown.
佐皮的老家也在那儿

42
00:05:57,374 --> 00:05:58,363
Need a job?
你要技工作吗?

43
00:05:58,894 --> 00:06:01,010
Yeah. Easy always trying to do better.
没错．伊斯总是尽力把事情做的最好

44
00:06:01,214 --> 00:06:06,049
Easy's one of a few coloured men around here who owns his own house.
伊斯在这个地方是少数几个拥有房子的黑人之

45
00:06:06,254 --> 00:06:09,485
He paying the mortgage every month, just like y'all folks.
他每个月都要换贷款就像你们这些家伙一样

46
00:06:10,014 --> 00:06:11,493
Property owner, huh?
拥有财产，喂?

47
00:06:12,094 --> 00:06:14,289
These big companies don't give a damn.
那些大公司根本就不会遭到谴责

48
00:06:14,494 --> 00:06:16,291
l got out of that racket long ago.
我早就离开那个飞机公司了

49
00:06:16,494 --> 00:06:20,692
lf you need a job, drop by this address, 7:00.
如果你需要一份工作7点来这个地方

50
00:06:21,254 --> 00:06:22,243
Tonight.
今晚

51
00:06:22,494 --> 00:06:24,212
What kind of work you do?
你是做什么的?

52
00:06:26,774 --> 00:06:28,173
l do favours.
我是来帮忙的

53
00:06:28,574 --> 00:06:30,405
l do favours for friends.
我来帮一个朋友

54
00:06:31,374 --> 00:06:32,523
Drop by.
顺便

55
00:06:37,094 --> 00:06:38,573
Who was that?
他是谁

56
00:06:38,814 --> 00:06:40,884
Just somebody l know. Businessman.
只是我认识的一个人做生意的

57
00:06:41,174 --> 00:06:43,324
-Businessman, huh? -Yeah, he is.
D做生意的，哈?D是的，没错

58
00:06:45,174 --> 00:06:46,846
Ain't nothing to worry about.
没有什么好紧张的

59
00:06:47,614 --> 00:06:50,333
When I'm told there's nothing to worry about...
当别人告诉我没有什么好紧张的时候．

60
00:06:50,574 --> 00:06:52,963
...I look to see if my fly is open.
我会看看我的拉链有没有开

61
00:06:54,054 --> 00:06:58,013
All the way home, all I thought about was a chance to make some money.
回家的时候，我一路上都在想怎样做个机会晚点钱

62
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:03,606
I first came out to Los Angeles when I got home from the war in Europe...
我刚到洛杉机的时候是我刚才欧洲打仗回来的时

63
00:07:04,014 --> 00:07:06,812
... with $300 in my pocket and the G.I. Bill.
口袋里只有300美金和一张军票

64
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:07,000
很多有色人种涌到德克萨斯州就像

65
00:07:07,174 --> 00:07:11,008
A lot of coloured folk from Texas and Louisiana moved to California...
大批的路易斯安娜州的人涌到加利福尼亚一样．．．

66
00:07:11,254 --> 00:07:14,849
... to get them good jobs in the shipyards and aircraft companies.
到造船厂和飞机制造厂去找一份比较好工作

67
00:07:16,894 --> 00:07:19,806
Now, me, myself, I was a machinist.
现在，我我本来是一个机械机工

68
00:07:20,054 --> 00:07:24,206
And the first thing I did when I saved enough money was to buy me a house.
也是第一份可以让我存钱买房子的工作

69
00:07:26,094 --> 00:07:28,688
Man, I loved coming home to my house.
嘿，我喜欢回到居于我自己的房子的感党

70
00:07:28,894 --> 00:07:29,804
I don't know.
我不知道

71
00:07:30,014 --> 00:07:32,608
I guess maybe I just loved owning something.
我想我只是很喜欢拥有某样东西的感党

72
00:07:42,854 --> 00:07:46,051
-l'll knock down the trees in the back. -Leave my trees alone.
我可以帮你把院子里的树砍掉D别动我的树

73
00:07:46,254 --> 00:07:48,404
Leave my trees! Get on!
别动我的树 走开

74
00:08:10,294 --> 00:08:12,808
I was feeling pretty desperate that evening.
那天晚上我感到很感到很绝望

75
00:08:13,934 --> 00:08:16,607
In a week, I'd be 2 months behind on my mortgage.
再过一星期，我的贷款就拖欠的时间就满2个月了

76
00:08:16,814 --> 00:08:18,884
And I wasn't about to lose my house.
而我不想失去我的房子

77
00:08:19,094 --> 00:08:22,291
But a chill running up the back of my neck was telling me...
但是一股塞战从我的背急串到我的脖子上

78
00:08:22,494 --> 00:08:24,530
...I was about to make a bad decision.
让我感觉到我会作出一个很坏的决定

79
00:08:24,894 --> 00:08:27,362
Yeah, Albright made me nervous.
是的，奥尔布赖特让我觉得紧张

80
00:08:27,574 --> 00:08:30,213
He reminded me of a fella in Texas named Mouse.
他让我想起了在德克萨斯州一个叫麦斯的家伙

81
00:08:30,654 --> 00:08:33,566
-Let's dump this thing. -Isn't this your friend's car?
我们开点把这部车开走这不你朋友的车吗?

82
00:08:33,774 --> 00:08:35,571
-What'd you do? -Just drive.
D你要干什么?你只要负责开车就好

83
00:08:35,774 --> 00:08:37,002
What did you do?
你都干了些什么?

84
00:09:05,054 --> 00:09:06,612
So, want the job?
你要做这个工作吗?

85
00:09:07,254 --> 00:09:08,607
lt depends.
看情况

86
00:09:09,094 --> 00:09:11,449
l don't wanna get mixed up in nothing.
我不想卷进任何是非里

87
00:09:12,854 --> 00:09:15,129
Walk out the door in the morning...
早上你走出那扇门的时候

88
00:09:16,094 --> 00:09:17,812
...you're mixed up in something.
你已经被卷进是非里了

89
00:09:19,054 --> 00:09:21,693
Only thing is, if you're mixed up to the top or not.
只有你是否在这个游戏中是否站上风的区别

90
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:24,806
l'm just looking for somebody. For a friend.
我只是在找人．帮一个朋友的忙

91
00:09:25,694 --> 00:09:27,093
Daphne Monet.
望芜“摩耐特

92
00:09:28,174 --> 00:09:31,803
Fianc茅e of Todd Carter. She's been gone two weeks.
托普卡特的未婚妻．她已经失踪2星期了

93
00:09:32,014 --> 00:09:34,972
lt upset the man so much, he stopped running for mayor.
他很伤心，他已经停止了竞选市长的活动了

94
00:09:36,374 --> 00:09:38,444
-l've never seen her. -That's a shame.
D我从未见过她．D你该感到羞“隗

95
00:09:40,614 --> 00:09:43,845
Daphne has a predilection for the company of Negroes.
望芜有跟黑人交朋友的偏好

96
00:09:44,094 --> 00:09:47,006
She likes jazz, pig's feet and dark meat.
她喜欢贾士乐猪脚和红肉

97
00:09:49,414 --> 00:09:50,847
'' Predilection.''
偏好

98
00:09:54,694 --> 00:09:57,003
l'd go looking for her myself...
我应该自己去找她的

99
00:09:57,294 --> 00:09:59,603
...but l'm not of the right persuasion.
但是我的说服力不够

100
00:10:00,494 --> 00:10:02,212
What do you want from me?
你要我做什么?

101
00:10:03,054 --> 00:10:04,407
What do you mean?
你是什么意思?

102
00:10:05,014 --> 00:10:07,084
-What do l do? -Get her location.
我的工作是什么?找到她

103
00:10:09,294 --> 00:10:11,410
Mr. Carter wants to make up with her.
卡特先生要和她修补关系

104
00:10:12,294 --> 00:10:13,568
$1 00.
100美金

105
00:10:14,414 --> 00:10:15,893
l pay in advance.
这是定金

106
00:10:21,814 --> 00:10:23,213
$1 00.
100美金

107
00:10:24,894 --> 00:10:26,566
To tell you where she's at?
告诉你她在哪就可以了吗?

108
00:10:26,774 --> 00:10:28,730
-That's right. -And that's all?
D没错就这些?

109
00:10:29,134 --> 00:10:29,930
That's all.
就这些

110
00:10:30,894 --> 00:10:34,250
Joppy tells me you used to frequent an illegal club.
佐皮告诉我你经常去一家非法经营的酒吧

111
00:10:34,494 --> 00:10:35,324
John's.
约翰酒吧

112
00:10:35,534 --> 00:10:38,002
Somebody saw Daphne there a few nights ago.
有人在几天前在那里看到她

113
00:10:39,174 --> 00:10:40,243
Start tonight.
从今天晚上开始

114
00:10:55,374 --> 00:10:57,604
Whoa, that's enough. Thank you.
哇，够了．谢谢

115
00:10:57,854 --> 00:11:00,414
-l'm gonna see you later. -All right, yeah.
我们迟点再见面D好的

116
00:11:44,614 --> 00:11:46,605
l told you it's a grocery store.
我告诉过你这里是杂货店

117
00:11:47,214 --> 00:11:49,444
How you doing, baby?
宝贝，你好吗?

118
00:11:50,854 --> 00:11:54,244
Mister, l told you, you can't be in here harassing folks.
先生，我告诉过你你不能在这儿妨碍我做生意

119
00:11:54,454 --> 00:11:55,523
What's going on?
发生了什么事情?

120
00:11:55,774 --> 00:11:59,210
l paid these damn cops off, and they're rousting my customers.
我付钱给这些该死的警察他们居然还赶走我的客人

121
00:11:59,774 --> 00:12:02,766
That's what he get for messing with that white woman.
那就是为什么会和那个白种女人站在那里

122
00:12:03,414 --> 00:12:05,052
Don't pay him no attention.
不要理他

123
00:12:05,254 --> 00:12:08,007
l done rung for Junior to take care of that.
我已经叫了姐尼尔下来处理这个事了

124
00:12:08,694 --> 00:12:11,083
They got nobody but Deucy and them tonight.
今天晚上他们只抓到了朵苗和那几个人

125
00:12:11,294 --> 00:12:14,604
l had Holiday on Thursday. Yeah, you missed it.
我星期四放假是的，你很想1

126
00:12:16,414 --> 00:12:19,212
Wait for the cops to leave. Take Easy upstairs.
等到警察走了以后再说吧带伊斯上楼

127
00:12:19,414 --> 00:12:23,453
And if he's still down here, come on back and throw his ass out.
如果他还站在这儿你就过来把他一脚揣出去

128
00:12:23,694 --> 00:12:25,969
Get out of here. You better be gone.
你就好现在就滚出去

129
00:12:26,174 --> 00:12:27,607
l'll be here waiting.
我会在这里等的

130
00:12:27,814 --> 00:12:30,647
You just wait, mister. Just keep waiting.
先生，那你就等吧慢慢等

131
00:12:30,854 --> 00:12:33,493
Mr. McGee, there is no upstairs.
麦墓尔先生这里只有一层

132
00:12:33,894 --> 00:12:35,646
-Got another cigarette? -Sure.
要再来一根吗?D当然

133
00:12:35,894 --> 00:12:38,010
Zapattas. How you smoke these damn things?
赞帕塔．你怎么会抽这些该死的东西

134
00:12:38,214 --> 00:12:40,569
You the only Negro smoke Mexican cigarettes.
你是唯一一个抽墨西哥雪茄的黑人

135
00:12:40,774 --> 00:12:43,607
Last time l heard these fellas was back in Houston.
上次我听说这些家伙回去休斯顿了

136
00:12:43,894 --> 00:12:46,010
The night Mouse pulled me off you.
那天晚上麦斯把我给甩开

137
00:12:46,214 --> 00:12:48,967
-That's how you remember it? -That's the way it was.
D你记得的是这样子的吗?D事实就是这样

138
00:12:49,174 --> 00:12:50,289
Look here...
听着

139
00:12:50,494 --> 00:12:53,247
...admit that you helped Mouse kill Navrochet.
你现在承认你帮麦斯杀死诺勒切了吧

140
00:12:53,454 --> 00:12:57,003
Get off that. You know l didn't have nothing to do with that.
好了．你知道这和我没有什么关系

141
00:13:01,214 --> 00:13:02,249
Where the white women?
那个白人女人在哪?

142
00:13:02,494 --> 00:13:04,325
-l pay them no mind. -l bet.
我没有注意过她们D我敢赌你有

143
00:13:04,574 --> 00:13:07,247
Like you didn't help Mouse kill his stepfather.
就像你没有帮麦斯杀他的继父一样

144
00:13:07,494 --> 00:13:10,247
Did you help him kill his stepbrother too?
你也帮他杀了的他继父的儿子吗?

145
00:13:35,774 --> 00:13:37,765
Give me a setup and a Coke back.
给我一杯可乐

146
00:13:38,494 --> 00:13:42,612
Have you seen a girl named Dahlia, Delila, something like that?
你有没有见一个女孩叫做望而尔朵而尔，或是类4以这样的名字?

147
00:13:42,814 --> 00:13:45,203
White girl, supposed to be something to see.
白人女孩有人在这里看见过她

148
00:13:46,014 --> 00:13:48,653
lf l do see her, l'll keep her to myself.
如果我看到她我一定会留着自己用

149
00:14:09,454 --> 00:14:10,330
Keep the change.
零钱给你了

150
00:14:12,774 --> 00:14:13,570
Deacon Odell.
迪森“欧戴尔

151
00:14:16,174 --> 00:14:17,653
How you doing tonight?
你好吗?

152
00:14:17,854 --> 00:14:20,288
lt's going all right. lt sure is going.
很好．怎么会不好

153
00:14:20,494 --> 00:14:22,450
Easy Rawlins, is that you?
伊斯．g林斯，是你吗?

154
00:14:23,574 --> 00:14:26,691
-Ain't jumped out of no windows yet? -Not yet, Dupree.
D你还没有摆脱失业的困境吗?D还没有，杜瑞

155
00:14:26,894 --> 00:14:29,692
-You know Coretta, don't you? -Sure, how you doing?
D你认识克拉塔，是吗?D当然，你好?

156
00:14:29,894 --> 00:14:30,849
l'm all right.
我很好

157
00:14:31,094 --> 00:14:32,652
This is Odell.
这是欧戴尔

158
00:14:35,414 --> 00:14:37,086
Can we sit with y'all?
我们可以跟你们一起坐吗?

159
00:14:38,174 --> 00:14:39,368
Sure.
当然

160
00:14:40,054 --> 00:14:42,488
We miss you down at the plant.
整个农场的人都很想你

161
00:14:42,694 --> 00:14:45,447
Benny would've gave you your job back, right?
班尼不会再把工作给回你了是吗?

162
00:14:45,694 --> 00:14:48,447
All you had to do was go and say you was sorry.
你只要去道歉就可以了

163
00:14:48,654 --> 00:14:50,804
l'm sorry, all right. Give me that bourbon.
好吧，我道歉．把波夯威士忌酒给我

164
